						</svg>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 text-center">Rising Energy Bills</h3>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						If your energy bills are steadily increasing despite consistent usage, your HVAC system may be losing
						efficiency. Newer models can be up to 50% more efficient, potentially saving you significant money on
						utility costs.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Inconsistent Temperatures -->
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 bg-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6 mx-auto">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
						     stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M12 3v1m0 16v1m9-9h-1M4 12H3m15.364 6.364l-.707-.707M6.343 6.343l-.707-.707m12.728 0l-.707.707M6.343 17.657l-.707.707M16 12a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0z"/>
						</svg>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 text-center">Inconsistent Temperatures</h3>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						If some rooms are too hot while others are too cold, or if your system struggles to maintain the temperature
						set on your thermostat, it may be time for a replacement that can provide more consistent comfort.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Unusual Noises or Odors -->
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 bg-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6 mx-auto">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
						     stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M15.536 8.464a5 5 0 010 7.072m2.828-9.9a9 9 0 010 12.728M5.586 15.536a5 5 0 01-.707-7.07m-2.122 9.9a9 9 0 010-12.728"/>
						</svg>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 text-center">Unusual Noises or Odors</h3>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						Strange sounds like grinding, banging, or squealing, or unusual odors coming from your HVAC system can
						indicate serious mechanical problems that may warrant replacement rather than repair.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Outdated Technology -->
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 bg-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6 mx-auto">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
